content: I apologize for any confusion, upon researching the lyrics of "Just Another Day" by Oingo Boingo, I was not able to find any literary references, the line "There's a golden coin, that reflects the sun" could be a metaphor to the hope that exists in the world, or the possibility of finding something positive even in the darkest of situations, and the way that light shines through the darkness. I apologize if my previous answer led to confusion.
